list.name: Changes
list.comment:
Refactor file organization and introduce search & sort utilities
File organization has been updated through moving various files to new directory structures better reflecting their functionalities. New sorting and search utility files have been added, though currently they are blank placeholders for future development. A BubbleSort implementation has also been included.

task.summary:
Add multiple utility classes and supporting schemas
A set of utility and schema classes are added to the project. This includes classes for generating hashed values, mock HTTP responses, and initializing user data, among others. Also, schemas for describing objects such as User and SObject have been introduced. This commit also includes changes to project settings and the addition of a .gitignore file.

Update project settings and add utility & schema classes
Several utility and schema classes have been added for functions like hashed value generation, mock HTTP responses, and user data initialization. Alongside this, the project settings have been adjusted, a .gitignore file introduced, and Apache Maven PMD Plugin has been included in the project dependencies.

Add new utility classes and update DataGenerator
Added NumberUtilities, StringUtilities, and StringActions utility classes for performing various operations on numbers and strings. Expanded the DataGenerator utility class to insert users and assign permissions. New classes include relevant documentation.

Add new utility files for date, array, sort, and date calculation
Added a DateUtility file for parsing formats and extracting information from date strings. Also added an ArrayUtility to handle array operations such as printing, insertion, deletion, searching, and sorting. In addition, created an empty SortUtilities file for future sorting algorithms and added a DateCalculator for calculating difference between two dates.

Implement StackHelper, QueueHelper and enhance ArrayUtility
Created StackHelper and QueueHelper classes to aid in operations involving stacks and queues. Additionally, enhanced ArrayUtility with more comprehensive functions including support for sorting methods, linear search, binary search, deletion of array elements, and duplicate checks.

Add APRCalculatorWithCompound class
Introduced a new class, APRCalculatorWithCompound, to calculate Annual Percentage Rate (APR) considering the compounding frequency. The method iteratively adjusts APR until the present value of the payments equals the loan amount and returns APR as a percentage. Test calculations are included in the main method.

Refactor file organization and introduce search & sort utilities
File organization has been updated through moving various files to new directory structures better reflecting their functionalities. New sorting and search utility files have been added, though currently they are blank placeholders for future development. A BubbleSort implementation has also been included.
